column5: So yesterday evening and this evening I was able to get some fishing in (1hr 45min both times).  Yesterday was better for numbers but today was better for the biggest fish.  All and all here are the numbers.  Yesterday 10x crappie landed, 1x blue gill and 2x rockbass.  Today was 8x crappie, 1x RB and 1x BIG pumpkin seed.  I think I'm finally starting to figure out crappie with soft plastics and I've never really targeted these fun little buggers.  Most fish were all palm size and well, I'd never keep any that size.  May try again Thurs is time and weather works in my favour...
Way to go Captain!  Cheers,  Mark
Crappie are super fun but those rock bass fight great!  I sincerely wish I could(or knew how) to Target them. I get maybe 15 a year
